President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in Tennessee and ordered Federal assistance to supplement state and local response efforts following an explosion on December 25, 2020. The Department of Homeland Security, Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), has been authorized to coordinate disaster relief efforts to help the local population and provide necessary assistance. FEMA will identify, mobilize, and provide equipment and resources as needed to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be provided at 75 percent Federal funding. Myra M. Shird has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.